social_posts.post_text: Just a heads up for anyone who is interested but I started taking commissions for MtG painted artist’s proofs! I only took a handful to start out so I don’t get stressed but if you’re interested in being added to the waiting list for the next bunch of open slots contact @donnycaltrider who’s my agent for these! Just a couple I made for friends so far to give an idea of what they’ll look like
My final MtG card was released yesterday! It’s Sagittarius/Forest. As always if you’re interested in bidding on the original contact @donnycaltrider ♐️✨
Blog entry about the Sagittarius/Forest card is up now on my website! You can find the link to the blog in my bio
Green Man fountain face on an Aquarius/Island proof for my sis in law @vampyreblues .
Painted Foil Leo/Plains AP for the upcoming show @donnycaltrider is curating for @gallerynucleus

I finally fired a little charm I sculpted in 2020 then made a push mold of so I could reproduce it in precious metal clay! I don’t know why I was so worried about trying to fire this, but it’s a really promising first attempt, and I’m very excited to get into trinket making. There’s some distortion from push molding and PMC shrinks when it fires as you can see but I think it held all the detail pretty well! The original sculpt was done on the back of a quarter. Thank you to @morgaine_faye for all the advice and encouragement when I had 100 questions about this wizardry.

It was revealed a couple days ago but I was waiting until I’d finished my blog entry about it to post here. Here’s the cover I painted for @upholsteredmusic ‘s new album Woven which drops tomorrow from my friend @exfkaty ‘s label @exoticfeverrecords . This was such a lovely project to work on and I was handed so many themes to bounce off of that were up my alley. If you check out my blog via the link in my bio I wrote a whole thing about the inspirations and process behind this one.

Received a copy of the very lovely Czech edition of @anyamartin99 ‘s Grass! I did this cover for the original @dimshores edition and when @nakladatelstvi_medusa translated it for publication he reached out about using my cover again as well as the black and white interior illustrations and I did new title text. They did such a good job on this book, the cover looks great matte with the glossy spot coat on the flower. I don’t know how many people who follow me speak Czech but if you do and you like freaky weird fiction check it out!

Now that people are starting to receive them I’ll be posting the first batch of painted mtg artists proofs I made. Here’s a 3 card set for Gemini/mountain-Aquarius/island-Aries/mountain. One of the options when getting proofs is a 3 card sun-moon-rising set. It’s a challenging scale and dimension even for someone who paints as small as I do, but it’s been fun to figure out. Doing these has also given me an excuse to use a bunch of metallic paints I don’t normally use for things that need to be reproduced since these are meant to be enjoyed in person not print. If you’re interested in commissioning a proof get in touch with @donnycaltrider

I’m going to start posting more of these painted MtG proofs now that people have received them! Most people opted to have me do something of my choosing connected to the sign on the card. The first one is a fiery Aries torch on the back of Aries/mountain and the second is referencing a bit of Persephone myth on the back of a Virgo/island. As usual if you want to commission one just reach out to @donnycaltrider and he’ll get you on the list!

Two more painted MtG APs. A Sekhmet on the back of a Leo/Plains and a sad eel pair writhing around a weeping gargoyle head on the back of a Pisces/island. As usual contact @donnycaltrider if you want to get on the next commission list

Another 3 card AP set! This one is Virgo/Aries/Libra. The figure representing Virgo is modeled after some images and sculptures of Mesopotamian women with inlaid eyes and jewelry I saw at the Morgan Library last month, in green inspired by both aged bronze and the green skin of Osiris. Libra represented by the weighing of the heart in the afterlife and a fiery dragon representing Aries and taking the place of Ammit
After the client saw the three card set in my previous post he requested a single card with a scarab painted on it as the the image has a personal meaning to him.

One more finished AP from the last batch before I start the ones from my next set! This was my first time with a Magic the Gathering specific request; Nicol Bolas. It’s an interesting challenge figuring out how to keep the features that make the character recognizable while making it your own style, but this ended up being one of my favorite cards I painted. I’m partial to the older more playful card art of him (by Ed Beard Jr.) vs. the big serious muscular style so I tried to split the difference somewhat

Some photos of a painting I actually finished last year for the reprint of my Gogol zine which is pretty close to being finished now. This is a scene from St John’s Eve which I originally wanted to illustrate when I started the series in 2015 but didn’t get to. It depicts the devil in disguise as a well dressed stranger who promises the story’s protagonist treasure but at a great cost. If you flip through you can see the sketch I did back in 2015, some images from Yuri Ilyenko’s film Eve of Ivan Kupalo (which I only just saw last month somehow!) depicting the same character, and a photo I took of a concrete grave marker in NJ which is where I got the design for the wooden cross here. I’m hoping to do a write up on my blog soon about the illustration series and some of the movies and folklore related to it.

Does instagram still work? Unclear. But here’s another for my extended Gogol zine which I’m almost finished with. This is from the story A May Night and it’s one of the scenes I originally wanted to illustrate in the original series and didn’t get to. I fished this a month or so ago but it’s challenging to photograph and I’m still not totally pleased with how it looks compared to the original but this will do for now.

A belated birthday Elric on the back of a Sagittarius/Forest AP for my BIL @the_wicker_dan . I had this drawn up months ago but was waiting on the cards. The background was inspired by my lava lamp and I’m probably going to try and replicate it on a bigger piece eventually. If you want to get on the waiting list for custom APs from me @donnycaltrider is putting together the list for the next batch. I’ll have a bunch of ones from the last batch to post once people receive them and then I’m going to take a break to finish some more personal projects!

Another finished AP! The client lives in Hawaii and collects AP’s with Hawaiian themed art. The card was my choice so I did this on the back of the Aries/Mountain card since it depicts a volcano. The subject is a legend that says Pele sends a white dog to warn people before eruptions and for all the plants I tried to pick ones that are native to Hawaii.  It was a fun theme to be given!

A 3 card set from my most recent batch of custom mtg AP commissions! This one was a gift for someone’s wife. She’s Scorpio sun/Gemini moon/ Capricorn rising. If you get one of these and Gemini is in your chart you’re pretty much guaranteed to get a pair of freaky little guardian beasts from me. As always if you want to commission a single or set @donnycaltrider can add you to the list.

Another three card MtG custom AP set! This client purchased a sun/moon/rising set in the last batch and this time gave me full reign to do any 3 cards as singles or a continuous image. Because his last set didn’t contain any earth signs I though that would be a cool theme. The image isn’t continuous but the images are all related. At some point I want to do air/fire/water sets too.

Another sun/moon/rising custom MtG AP set! This one was for someone’s child who is Pisces/Aquarius/Cancer. There was an obvious theme in this combination (despite Aquarius being an air sign, symbolism wise it is quite wet). The octopus motif on the vessel comes from Minoan pottery but the shape of the pointed bottom comes from a kind of Greek amphora often found in shipwrecks.

A couple more singles from my last batch of MtG APs. The first one is on the back of an Aquarius/Island card. The request was for “something Aquarius themed or year of the tiger themed” so I combined the two and made a tiger vessel. The second one is on the back of a Pisces/Island and the request was for “a zodiac themed Urza”. The character design for Urza is really far from my style so I struggled a bit but I think I style managed to make him recognizable

A couple more single MtG AP proofs. These were on the back of Cancer/island and Aries/mountain cards, both requests were for something to fit the sign/card art and they both coincidentally have the same color scheme

Another 3 card MtG AP set. This one is Scorpio/Libra/Virgo and it’s a memorial. It took me a while to work out how to combine the sign elements in a way that was appropriate. I’m happy with how it came out though and hope it’s some comfort to the person who commissioned it.
We’re celebrating @toothpasta ‘s bday at work today and when asked what she wanted on the back of a Cancer MtG AP she requested a “sexy crab girl”. Happy birthday you little freak

Gonna try and get my account 👁️ again with an art post! This is a set of 7 custom AP’s for a client building a deck inspired by his homeland of China. The request was for four mountain cards incorporating his personal astrological assignments and Karst mountains from where he grew up: dragon, monkey king, ram and crab. I based the appearance of the monkey king partly on the costuming he appears in in Chinese opera, and the crab is inspired by the Chinese mitten crab. The second part of the request was for three forest cards also inspired by Chinese culture. I decided to represent the four auspicious beasts; black tortoise, white tiger, vermillion bird and the fourth is the Azure Dragon from the mountain set. The vermillion bird is somewhat inspired by a Chinese pheasant and the three plants in the background of each are the three friends of winter; bamboo, pine, and plum. The client also requested the characters for mountain and forest be added to each card as these will actually be played with as part of his custom themed deck! This ended up being a very fun set to make and I enjoyed the challenge of making them coherent to exist as a set and trying to make them consistent with my personal style. My commissions are open for more APs so feel free to contact @donnycaltrider about setting one up!

Protests and other disruptions require a lot of noise so @illustro_obscurum and I found these big bells at five below and painted them. We had been bringing improvised noisemakers with us previously, in the form of talenti containers full of tamarind seeds. You could easily make something similar with any plastic container and dried beans maybe pennies too. What I am saying is this moment requires you to be extremely loud and disruptive in whatever ways you are able, within whatever social structures you inhabit. Quick and easy sign making. Find a nice corrugated plastic sign on the roadside, cut stencils from poster board (or cardboard soda carton or whatever), spraypaint it.  To make sure it’s legible light colors on dark or dark on light, value matters more than hue usually. I make mine two sided so they see me coming and going and I can say more. To make stencils last longer you can “laminate” them with packing tape. The sign itself will be totally waterproof, won’t run if you get caught in the rain or crumple and get mushy. You can also be much neater than I was masking areas off but I was in a hurry. Philly see you soon. Ceasefire now, end the blockade, end the occupation.
